modelling studies</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the accuracy </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">will depe</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">nd on the robustness </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">and availability of</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> data</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">nd the so</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">phistication of the modelling techniques</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> applied</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">RAC does not regard itself as having sufficient knowledge to be able to comment on</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> the adequacy of</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> either of these.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 12.74pt; padding-left:5.26pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">H</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ow can we improve the reliability and efficiency of travel on the strategic road net</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">work? What impact will new technology have?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Reliability and efficiency will improve through the removal of bottlenecks, the further improvement of driver information so that road users can select routes that are least congested and improvements to the spe</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ed and efficiency with which incidents are dealt with. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The removal of bottlenecks is </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">a </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">fundamental </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">benefit </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">of the RIS. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Driver information has improved steadily in recent years. The </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">current </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">m</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">anaged </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">m</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">otorways programme </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">has improved the quality of information available </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">for journey planning</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">this</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> information is </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">also </span><span style="font-family:Cal