pt">will </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">respond </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">un</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">favourably if they have to</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">provide</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> additional funding for something that they believe they are already paying for. T</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">he RAC is</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> willing and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> able to canvas its members, both individual</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and busi</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">nesses, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">to test their views on alternative funding models.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 12.74pt; padding-left:5.26pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">How should the Highways</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> Agency be refor</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">med to make it ‘</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">the world’s leading highway operator</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">’</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">? What roles should Government and the private sector play to ensure better management of the strategic road network?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The decision to follow the recommendations of the Cook Report and make the Highways Agency a more commercial entity that is still ultimately responsible to the Government is a welcome move which should bring benefits for road users. In order to deliver the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> RIS, the Agency needs the freedom to hire the best people and to operate in a manner that delivers improved performance and value for money. The constraints within </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">which a </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Government </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Agency </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">operate</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">are </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">not designed either</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> for</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> delivery of major infrastruc</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ture projects or to operate national assets of the scale and complexity of the national roads network.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">We have already commented </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">earlier in this paper </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">on the need for a Roads Regulator and the roles of existing </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">organisations</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> representing road users.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">IN S</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">UMMARY</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">RAC generally welcomes Action for Roads as a genuine attempt </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">to break</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> out of the short term planning and investment </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">cycle </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">that has led to the degeneration of our roads into a state that is unfit for purpose and incapable of supporting economic grow</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">th</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The majority of benefits of the first RIS will not be delivered until towards the end of the next parliament and more urgent action is needed to address the crumbling state of local roads</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Action for Roads proposes that the RIS will be backed by </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">legislation. The RAC believes that this is fundamental to success along with actions to restructure the Highways Agency into a more commercial organisation, the establishment of a Roads Regulator and the harnessing of existing road user representatives to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ensure Road Users have an influential voice capable of influencing those accountable for the performance of all roads</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">October 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">1</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>